 The Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, has described as a healthy development, the decision of the South-East Governors Forum to summon the courage to call for the release of its leader, Nnamdi Kanu from illegal detention in Abuja. April 4, 2017 In "News" South-East governors, yesterday, justified the proscription of the Indigenous People of Biafra (IPoB), saying the action was to douse tension and end loss of lives in the region. September 17, 2017 In "News" TIME was when most Igbo people admired the courage of Mazi Nnamdi Kanu, the Umuahia –born leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, IPOB, and the director of Radio Biafra, for boldly speaking out in defense of his people, at a time it appeared that the Igbo elite had chickened… July 8, 2017 In "Politics"